.:: Puzzle 4x3-Level-2-9::.
There are 3 different favourite beverages: hot-chocolate, mirinda, iced-tea
There 3 different types of food: corn, orange, cauliflower
There are 3 different nationalities: australian, canadian, argentine
The people use 3 different means of transport: helicopter, tram, subway
1. the person driving the subway is between the canadian and the argentine##2
2. the person eating cauliflower is on the right of the person drinking mirinda##1
3. the person drinking hot-chocolate is on the far left##1
4. the person eating orange is on the far left##1
5. the australian is on the left of the person driving the tram##1
6. the person driving the tram is the canadian##1

.:: Answer ::.
|               |    1     |      2      |    3     |
| Beverage      | hot-chocolate      | mirinda | iced-tea     |
| Food          | orange   | corn      | cauliflower     |
| Nationality   | argentine  | australian      | canadian |
| Transport     | helicopter | subway        | tram     |

